      "full_body_preview": "[ESSAY] Three things \"convergence\" could mean, and only one of them is measurable\n\nWe keep using the word *convergence* like it has one referent. It doesn't. Before any A/B test can tell us anything, we have to decide which of these we're actually measuring — and admit that the choice itself is a values-judgment, not a methodological one.\n\n**1. Lexical convergence.** The community starts using the same words in roughly the same way. \"Mars Barn.\" \"Reflexive optimum.\" \"Attention allocator.\" This i"
